Commentary Text: Bumrah to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! This is the Bumrah we all know of. Searing short ball at Nitish Rana's face, he was caught in awkward tangle, held up the bat as a shield to protect himself, the ball kisses the top-hand glove and the umpire did not pick it. Rules it not out but Ishan Kishan was convinced as was Bumrah, Rohit took the review and UltraEdge does its job. What an over this is. Totally turned it around. Nitish Rana c Ishan Kishan b Bumrah 43(26) [4s-3 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Russell to Pollard, out Pollard Run Out!! 1 run completed. Mumbai's last flicker of hope has been extinguished by KKR! And what drama to conclude his stay as well. Sharp short ball from Russell, forced Pollard into the pull and the top edge went up many-a-mile. Always a tough catch for Jackson who tried his best, got across and dived forward but couldn't latch onto the catch. Amidst all this, Pollard is stranded mid-pitch and can't get back in time. Varun is alert and covers up for Jackson, firing a flat throw to the keeper's end where an alert Shreyas has already reached for it. Great awareness from the skipper and Pollard is gone by a mile. Pollard run out (Chakaravarthy/Shreyas Iyer) 15(16) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Cummins to Kumar Kartikeya, out Kumar Kartikeya Run Out!! 1 run completed. Suicidal second run and Kartikeya is not even in the frame! Probably was forced to go for it, given that it was the last ball of the over and Pollard had to get strike for the next. The second was never on though. This went off the toe-end of the bat, after Kartikeya shuffled across the stumps early and got lucky that he wasn't hit on the pad or bowled. Trickled to deep square leg and Rahane even with a bad throw could have gotten this run out. But well, he fires a flat accurate throw to Jackson who does the rest. Kumar Kartikeya run out (Rahane/Jackson) 3(5)

Commentary Text: Cummins to Murugan Ashwin, out Caught by Chakaravarthy!! And Cummins replicates Bumrah with a triple-wicket over! MI are imploding in sensational fashion here and it's that short of a length spot that's doing all the damage. Ashwin knows he can't negotiate it standing still, and so backs away, forcing Cummins to follow him and then opts for the ramp. Not a bad option, except that third man is in place and quite fine too, precisely for this sort of an adventure. Right down to Varun who times his leap well to take a nice overhead catch. Murugan Ashwin c Chakaravarthy b Cummins 0(2)

Commentary Text: Cummins to Daniel Sams, out Caught by Jackson!! Double strike from Cummins! Is this the game-defining over? Bumrah bowled at around this point earlier on in the game and deflated KKR completely. It's Cummins' turn now. No compassion for his fellow countryman at all as his bangs this into that hard length, cramping the batter for room as well but Sams decides to slog anyway and gets a huge top-edge that crashes into his helmet and balloons towards Jackson. Regulation take and Sams walks off a bit groggy. Daniel Sams c Jackson b Cummins 1(2)

Commentary Text: Cummins to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Cummins with a massive breakthrough! Gee, this game just continues to ebb and flow at blistering pace. That short ball has been of great efficiency on this surface tonight and trust Australia's premier fast bowler to hit that spot with pace. Well-directed bumper and Kishan is forced into an aggressive pull stroke. Huge top-edge and it's another sky-kisser towards fine leg. Rinku is safe as houses though and clings on to the pressure catch. Ishan Kishan c Rinku Singh b Cummins 51(43) [4s-5 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Chakaravarthy to Tim David, out Caught by Rahane!! And this is a massive strike from Chakaravarthy! The in-form David holes out to the deep. With the asking rate creeping, he knew he had to target someone and as MI were playing Narine safely, they couldn't afford to do that with one more bowler. David feels Chakaravarthy has to go and tries the slog sweep but neither is the length there nor is he close to the pitch of this for the shot. Massive top-edge, goes up in the air for miles and straight down long-on's throat. This might be statistically Chakaravarthy's wicket but it's been created by that sensational Narine over. Tim David c Rahane b Chakaravarthy 13(9) [4s-3]

Commentary Text: Russell to Ramandeep Singh, out Caught by Nitish Rana!! Russell comes back on, and strikes again! Ramandeep's innings hadn't gotten anywhere and he knew he had to up the ante a little bit to relieve his partner of the pressure. Looks to go across the line with a fiery pull shot but Russell hasn't offered any pace on this short ball, big miscue and it only goes as far as backward point. MI are just not getting that momentum kick in this chase. This partnership did well to arrest those early strikes but couldn't get the scoring rate going. Ramandeep Singh c Nitish Rana b Russell 12(16)

Commentary Text: Southee to Rohit, out Caught by Jackson!! This is a lucky, lucky breakthrough for KKR. Southee was smart to bowl the scrambled seam short of length delivery, Ro was cramped by the angle and he was jumping to tuck it to leg. Ball flew off the thigh pad and Jackson took a good low catch diving to the right. He was convinced there was an edge and asked the captain to review. It took ages to build UltraEdge. Even on the reply it is very evident that the spikes were caught before the ball touched the bat. There was one as the as passed the bat and the third ump didn't take long to make the call when he could have taken some time. Maybe he went by having what evidence he had. Rohit definitely not happy. Didn't seem to have hit that. Rohit c Jackson b Southee 2(6)
